  "title": "Resident Architect",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>• Minimum 8 years of architectural experience with recognized Diploma in relevant field, and at least 5 years of experience in construction supervision for projects of similar scale and complexity in local context.</p><p>• Work as Resident Architecture to our LTA projects, to assist and report to RE and SRE to monitor all site activities, and any incident, including near misses. Report any non-compliance to RE and Qualified Person Supervision (QPS).</p><p>• Assist Engineer in carrying out supervision for related works include but not limited to replacement and extension, construction and reconfiguration of viaduct/bridge works, and associated civil works, proposed new flexible pavement and infrastructure, re-alignment of roadways, fencing and construction.</p><p>• Good knowledge and well versed in Singapore building regulations and codes, design development & detailing.</p><p>• Supervise all construction activities and ensure compliance to all plans/drawings, risk assessment and specifications.</p><p>• Willing to work on rotation shifts.</p><p>• Ensure compliance to all health and safety policies.</p><p>• Ensure that contractor and their subcontractor comply with client's safety requirement, and safety checklists are follow.</p><p>• Must be capable of being a Team Leader and take responsibility in managing projects independently without supervision.</p><p>• Assist RE to manage and maintain records and documentation on field or site changes and to monitor adherence to construction schedule.</p><p>• The Resident Architecture shall be dedicated full time on Site, not less than 6 months before BSC until CWW is obtained.</p><p>• Carryout standing supervision for critical site activities based.</p><p>• Preferably PR and Singaporean.</p>",
